Computer Vision Car Identifier Model Demo

Objective

The objective of this project is to showcase a proof of concept of a vehicle's make model identifier utilizing computer vision tools. In this project I make use Resnet 50 neural model trained on the Stanford Cars dataset in regards to classifying car makes and models. A metric of 97% accuracy with 18 epochs was obtained in testing with the Stanford testing dataset. Although the data is from older cars from early 2010s and prior, the model is still able of identyfing the most similar car to any newer car even for makes that were never in its dataset. Image and video examples are showcased below.

%%capture
device = "cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu"

net = models.resnet50(weights=None)
net.fc = nn.Linear(net.fc.in_features, 196)
net.load_state_dict(torch.load("/content/drive/MyDrive/cars196_head_frozen.pth", map_location=device))
net.eval().to(device)

root = kagglehub.dataset_download("eduardo4jesus/stanford-cars-dataset")
meta = scipy.io.loadmat(os.path.join(root, "car_devkit", "devkit", "cars_meta.mat"))
labels = [c[0] for c in meta["class_names"][0]]

tf_infer = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize(224),
    transforms.ToTensor(),
    transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225])
])
In[]:
def classify(pil_img):
    with torch.no_grad():
        t = tf_infer(pil_img).unsqueeze(0).to(device)
        idx = net(t).argmax(1).item()
    return labels[idx]

yolo = YOLO("yolov8n.pt")
In[]:
def process_image(img_path):
    frame = cv2.imread(img_path)
    r = yolo.track(frame, persist=False, classes=[2])
    if r and r[0].boxes is not None:
        for x1, y1, x2, y2 in r[0].boxes.xyxy.int().tolist():
            crop = Image.fromarray(cv2.cvtColor(frame[y1:y2, x1:x2], cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
            print(classify(crop))
In[]:
def process_video(video):
    ret = []
    seen = set()                               # remember track IDs
    cap  = cv2.VideoCapture(video)
    yolo = YOLO("yolov8n.pt")

    while True:
        ok, frame = cap.read()
        if not ok:
            break

        r = yolo.track(frame,
                       persist=True,
                       classes=[2],            # cars only
                       conf=0.40,              # raise confidence
                       verbose=False)

        if r and r[0].boxes is not None:
            boxes = r[0].boxes
            ids   = boxes.id
            ids   = ids.int().tolist() if ids is not None else [-1]*len(boxes)

            for (x1, y1, x2, y2), tid in zip(boxes.xyxy.int().tolist(), ids):
                if tid in seen:               # already handled this car
                    continue
                seen.add(tid)
                crop = Image.fromarray(cv2.cvtColor(frame[y1:y2, x1:x2],
                                                   cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
                ret.append(classify(crop))

    cap.release()
    return ret

from PIL import Image
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

print("The correct answer is that the car is a BMW M5 , below is the model's guess:")
process_image("/content/drive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/test1.jpg")
img = Image.open("/content/drive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/test1.jpg")
plt.imshow(img)
plt.axis("off")
plt.show()

The correct answer is that the car is a BMW M5 , below is the model's guess:

0: 352x640 1 car, 180.6ms
